<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-40-0145 </DOCNO><TEXT>The South African coal industry entered a recession in 1986 which worsenedin 1987 with sanctions being imposed. The outlook for 1988 continuesto look bleak though domestic sales should increase. The key factorswhich will determine the industry's future performance are: export volumes;export sales prices; local sales volumes; production and transport costs;and foreign currency exchange rates. An analysis is presented of worldcoal reserves, major producers, major consumers, current and potentialmajor coal exporters, future world growth potential, port costs and internationalfreight rates, coal requirements of Eskom, Sasol and Iscor and cost analysis.15 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>